Alembic migrations for the mathingo backend.

Generic single-database configuration with an async engine
(SQLAlchemy 2.0 + asyncpg). The DATABASE_URL is read from the
application's pydantic settings in env.py — alembic.ini does not
hold any credentials.

To create a new revision after model changes:
    docker compose exec backend alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<message>"

To apply migrations:
    docker compose exec backend alembic upgrade head
